description:
File: lichen/subsys/lichen/routing/announce.c
Lines: 183-188, 305-308

In notify_observers():

    for (size_t i = 0U; i < count; i++) {
        int ret = observers[i].cb(announce, meta, observers[i].user_data);
        if (ret < 0) {
            return ret;  // <-- Early return on error
        }
        ...
    }

In lichen_announce_ingest_authenticated():

    ret = notify_observers(&announce, meta, seq_stale_for_pin);
    if (ret < 0) {
        k_mutex_unlock(&ingest_mutex);
        return ret;  // <-- Exit without updating peer state
    }

If an observer callback returns an error:
1. notify_observers returns early
2. lichen_announce_ingest_authenticated returns early
3. The peer's seq_num and location_seq_num are NOT updated

On the next announce from the same peer with the same sequence number:
- The peer lookup finds the old seq_num
- The announce appears 'new' again (seq_stale_for_pin may be false)
- Observers are notified again for the same announce

This can cause duplicate processing of announces if any observer is temporarily failing.
